<item>
            <title>[DATAREST-103] Add support for non-CrudRepositories</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/DATAREST-103</link>
                <project id="10901" key="DATAREST">Spring Data REST</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently only repositories implementing &lt;tt&gt;CrudRepository&lt;/tt&gt; can be used with Spring Data REST. Spring Data Commons now also exposes non-&lt;tt&gt;CrudRepository&lt;/tt&gt; instances.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We should rewrite the repository invocation parts to detect the CRUD methods necessary on the repository and provide a generic API to invoke these methods from clients without having to worry about pagination, id conversion etc.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We also should treat &lt;tt&gt;CrudRepository&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;PagingAndSortingRepository&lt;/tt&gt; as special cases and try to work around the reflection calls generally necessary for custom repositories.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
